{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YUNFM7dkkDMN47ZT1UKEyV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package web\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"net/http\"\n     8→\t\"net/http/httptest\"\n     9→\t\"testing\"\n    10→\t\"time\"\n    11→\n    12→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/sqlite\"\n    13→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    14→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    15→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    16→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    17→)\n    18→\n    19→// mockContainerManager implements ContainerManager for testing.\n    20→type mockContainerManager struct {\n    21→\tcontainers map[string]bool // containerID -> exists\n    22→\trunning    map[string]bool // containerID -> running\n    23→\tremoved    []string\n    24→}\n    25→\n    26→func newMockContainerManager() *mockContainerManager {\n    27→\treturn &mockContainerManager{\n    28→\t\tcontainers: map[string]bool{},\n    29→\t\trunning:    map[string]bool{},\n    30→\t}\n    31→}\n    32→\n    33→func (m *mockContainerManager) Logs(_ context.Context, containerID string) (string, error) {\n    34→\treturn \"mock logs\", nil\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→func (m *mockContainerManager) Remove(_ context.Context, containerID string) error {\n    38→\tif !m.containers[containerID] {\n    39→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"container %s not found\", containerID)\n    40→\t}\n    41→\tdelete(m.containers, containerID)\n    42→\tm.removed = append(m.removed, containerID)\n    43→\treturn nil\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→func (m *mockContainerManager) Inspect(_ context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error) {\n    47→\tif !m.containers[containerID] {\n    48→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"container %s not found\", containerID)\n    49→\t}\n    50→\treturn &ports.ContainerStatus{Running: m.running[containerID], ExitCode: 0}, nil\n    51→}\n    52→\n    53→func setupHandler(t *testing.T) (*Handler, *sqlite.Store) {\n    54→\tt.Helper()\n    55→\tstore, err := sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")\n    56→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    57→\tt.Cleanup(func() { store.Close() })\n    58→\n    59→\th, err := NewHandler(store, store)\n    60→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    61→\treturn h, store\n    62→}\n    63→\n    64→func seedRun(t *testing.T, store *sqlite.Store, id, workflow string, state domain.RunState) {\n    65→\tt.Helper()\n    66→\tseedRunWithProject(t, store, id, workflow, state, \"\")\n    67→}\n    68→\n    69→func seedRunWithProject(t *testing.T, store *sqlite.Store, id, workflow string, state domain.RunState, projectDir string) {\n    70→\tt.Helper()\n    71→\tctx := context.Background()\n    72→\trun := domain.NewRun(id, workflow)\n    73→\trun.ProjectDir = projectDir\n    74→\tif state != domain.RunStatePending {\n    75→\t\trun.Start()\n    76→\t\trun.ContainerID = \"abc123def456789\"\n    77→\t}\n    78→\tif state == domain.RunStateSucceeded || state == domain.RunStateFailed {\n    79→\t\trun.Complete(state)\n    80→\t}\n    81→\tif state == domain.RunStateFailed {\n    82→\t\trun.ErrorMessage = \"something went wrong\"\n    83→\t}\n    84→\trequire.NoError(t, store.CreateRun(ctx, run))\n    85→}\n    86→\n    87→func TestRunsList_WithRuns(t *testing.T) {\n    88→\th, store := setupHandler(t)\n    89→\tseedRun(t, store, \"test-run-1\", \"develop\", domain.RunStateRunning)\n    90→\tseedRun(t, store, \"test-run-2\", \"deploy\", domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n    91→\n    92→\treq := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/runs\", nil)\n    93→\tw := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    94→\th.ServeHTTP(w, req)\n    95→\n    96→\tassert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, w.Code)\n    97→\tassert.Contains(t, w.Header().Get(\"Content-Type\"), \"text/html\")\n    98→\tbody := w.Body.String()\n    99→\tassert.Contains(t, body, \"test-run-1\")\n   100→\tassert.Contains(t, body, \"test-run-2\")"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Undem5Yu7kXDhdHVyWzap8","session_id":"574c1595-2097-4277-9692-dc2a13d938c4","uuid":"083881a5-0a02-4693-b0f5-6fda21533218"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a5a0eff13cd376533","tool_use_id":"toolu_01Undem5Yu7kXDhdHVyWzap8","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore web handler and templates","usage":{"total_tokens":52251,"tool_uses":10,"duration_ms":24903},"uuid":"4c0758ad-f646-432a-80d7-2db9da41be32","session_id":"574c1595-2097-4277-9692-dc2a13d938c4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Undem5Yu7kXDhdHVyWzap8","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive analysis of the code.\n\n## Summary: Web Handler & Frontend Templates Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly reviewed all the web handler code and frontend templates. Here's what I found about the Prompts section expansion and how it works:\n\n### Key Files Analyzed:\n\n1. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go** (1301 lines) - Main web handler\n2. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html** - Project detail page with Prompts section\n3. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html** - Base HTML layout\n4. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css** - Styling for Prompts section\n5. Other templates: runs.html, run_detail.html, projects.html\n\n---\n\n## How the Prompts Section Works\n\n### Frontend (JavaScript in project_detail.html, lines 89-121):\n\nThe Prompts section expansion uses **git log history** to display commit information:\n\n```javascript\nfunction loadProjectInfo() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/info')\n        .then(r => r.json())\n        .then(data => {\n            // ... builds HTML with prompt files\n            if (data.prompt_files && data.prompt_files.length > 0) {\n                // For each prompt file:\n                pf.history.forEach(h => {\n                    // Displays: SHA, Date, Commit Message\n                    html += h.sha + ' ' + h.date + ' ' + h.message\n                })\n                // User can click each commit to toggle diff view\n            }\n        })\n}\n\nfunction toggleDiff(el) {\n    // Fetches diff when user clicks a history entry\n    fetch('/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=...&sha=...')\n        .then(r => r.text())\n        .then(text => { /* displays diff in pre block */ })\n}\n```\n\n### Backend (handler.go):\n\n#### Endpoint 1: `handleAPIProjectInfo` (lines 939-1025)\n**Purpose:** Returns prompt file metadata INCLUDING git commit history\n\n**Key code:**\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // ... resolves project directory ...\n    \n    // Reads Dockerfile for Docker image (lines 945-959)\n    // Reads version file (lines 961-968)\n    \n    // GET PROMPT FILES WITH GIT HISTORY (lines 970-1017):\n    promptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n    for _, e := range os.ReadDir(promptsDir) {\n        relPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n        \n        // RUN GIT LOG TO GET COMMIT HISTORY:\n        cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \n                          \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n        cmd.Dir = dir\n        out, err := cmd.Output()\n        \n        // Parse git output into commit entries:\n        // SHA | Date | Commit Message\n        for _, line := range strings.Split(string(out), \"\\n\") {\n            parts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n            history = append(history, commitEntry{\n                SHA:     parts[0][:7],      // Short SHA\n                Date:    dateStr,           // Parsed to YYYY-MM-DD\n                Message: parts[2],          // Commit message\n            })\n        }\n        \n        promptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{\n            Path:    relPath,\n            History: history,\n        })\n    }\n    \n    // Returns JSON with prompt_files containing history\n}\n```\n\n#### Endpoint 2: `handleAPIPromptDiff` (lines 1027-1056)\n**Purpose:** Fetch the actual diff for a specific commit\n\n**Key code:**\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    file := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n    sha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n    \n    // Validates SHA is hex (prevents injection)\n    for _, c := range sha {\n        if !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || ...) {\n            http.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n            return\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // RUNS GIT DIFF:\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n    cmd.Dir = dir\n    out, err := cmd.Output()\n    \n    // Returns unified diff as plain text\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n    w.Write(out)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why It Shows Git Commits Instead of File Contents\n\nThe design is **intentional**: The Prompts section displays **git history** to show how prompt files have evolved over time. When you expand the `<details>` element, you see:\n\n1. A list of commits that modified each prompt file\n2. Each entry shows: Short SHA + Date + Commit message\n3. Click any entry to see the `git diff` showing what changed in that commit\n\n**It does NOT show file contents directly** because:\n- The focus is on tracking changes (audit trail)\n- Users can see the evolution of prompts across commits\n- The diff view shows what was added/removed in each commit\n\n---\n\n## Key CSS Classes (style.css):\n\n```css\n/* Details/pre styling (lines 197-221) */\ndetails { margin: 0.5rem 0; }\ndetails summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; }\ndetails pre { background: var(--bg-surface); max-height: 400px; overflow: auto; }\n\n/* Diff block styling (lines 550-563) */\n.diff-block {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    padding: 0.5rem;\n    font-family: var(--mono);\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    max-height: 300px;\n    overflow: auto;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Important Implementation Details:\n\n1. **Git Integration**: Uses `os/exec` to run `git log` and `git diff` commands directly\n2. **Project Root**: All paths are relative to the project directory (`dir`)\n3. **Prompt File Location**: `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n4. **History Format**: `git log --format=%H %aI %s` (Full SHA, ISO8601 date, subject)\n5. **Diff Validation**: SHA is validated as hexadecimal before use (prevents command injection)\n6. **Styling**: Uses CSS `<details>` elements for expandable sections with `.diff-block` pre-formatted text\n\n---\n\n## Related Endpoints:\n\nThere are other file/content endpoints that serve **actual file contents** (not git history):\n\n- **`handleAPIStepContent`** (lines 1134-1199): Serves step prompt/script files from disk\n- **`handleAPIStepOutput`** (lines 563-634): Serves step execution output logs\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (lines 1058-1132): Parses workflow DSL files\n\nBut these are different from the Prompts section, which is exclusively git-history-based."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a5a0eff13cd376533 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54021\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 24908</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"574c1595-2097-4277-9692-dc2a13d938c4","uuid":"25edb2f7-3d7c-46d2-b8d1-568fa9cf36fd","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the web handler code and frontend templates/static files related to the project info page and prompts section. Look at:\n1. internal/adapters/web/handler.go - especially any endpoints for project info or prompts\n2. Any HTML templates or static JS files in internal/adapters/web/ that render the Prompts section\n3. Any endpoint that serves file contents vs git log\n\nI need to understand how the Prompts section expansion works and why it might be showing git commits instead of file contents. Be very thorough - read the full handler.go file and all template/static files.","agentId":"a5a0eff13cd376533","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive analysis of the code.\n\n## Summary: Web Handler & Frontend Templates Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly reviewed all the web handler code and frontend templates. Here's what I found about the Prompts section expansion and how it works:\n\n### Key Files Analyzed:\n\n1. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go** (1301 lines) - Main web handler\n2. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html** - Project detail page with Prompts section\n3. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html** - Base HTML layout\n4. **/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css** - Styling for Prompts section\n5. Other templates: runs.html, run_detail.html, projects.html\n\n---\n\n## How the Prompts Section Works\n\n### Frontend (JavaScript in project_detail.html, lines 89-121):\n\nThe Prompts section expansion uses **git log history** to display commit information:\n\n```javascript\nfunction loadProjectInfo() {\n    fetch('/api/projects/' + encodeURIComponent(projectLabel) + '/info')\n        .then(r => r.json())\n        .then(data => {\n            // ... builds HTML with prompt files\n            if (data.prompt_files && data.prompt_files.length > 0) {\n                // For each prompt file:\n                pf.history.forEach(h => {\n                    // Displays: SHA, Date, Commit Message\n                    html += h.sha + ' ' + h.date + ' ' + h.message\n                })\n                // User can click each commit to toggle diff view\n            }\n        })\n}\n\nfunction toggleDiff(el) {\n    // Fetches diff when user clicks a history entry\n    fetch('/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=...&sha=...')\n        .then(r => r.text())\n        .then(text => { /* displays diff in pre block */ })\n}\n```\n\n### Backend (handler.go):\n\n#### Endpoint 1: `handleAPIProjectInfo` (lines 939-1025)\n**Purpose:** Returns prompt file metadata INCLUDING git commit history\n\n**Key code:**\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // ... resolves project directory ...\n    \n    // Reads Dockerfile for Docker image (lines 945-959)\n    // Reads version file (lines 961-968)\n    \n    // GET PROMPT FILES WITH GIT HISTORY (lines 970-1017):\n    promptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n    for _, e := range os.ReadDir(promptsDir) {\n        relPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n        \n        // RUN GIT LOG TO GET COMMIT HISTORY:\n        cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \n                          \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n        cmd.Dir = dir\n        out, err := cmd.Output()\n        \n        // Parse git output into commit entries:\n        // SHA | Date | Commit Message\n        for _, line := range strings.Split(string(out), \"\\n\") {\n            parts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n            history = append(history, commitEntry{\n                SHA:     parts[0][:7],      // Short SHA\n                Date:    dateStr,           // Parsed to YYYY-MM-DD\n                Message: parts[2],          // Commit message\n            })\n        }\n        \n        promptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{\n            Path:    relPath,\n            History: history,\n        })\n    }\n    \n    // Returns JSON with prompt_files containing history\n}\n```\n\n#### Endpoint 2: `handleAPIPromptDiff` (lines 1027-1056)\n**Purpose:** Fetch the actual diff for a specific commit\n\n**Key code:**\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    file := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n    sha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n    \n    // Validates SHA is hex (prevents injection)\n    for _, c := range sha {\n        if !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || ...) {\n            http.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n            return\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // RUNS GIT DIFF:\n    cmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n    cmd.Dir = dir\n    out, err := cmd.Output()\n    \n    // Returns unified diff as plain text\n    w.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n    w.Write(out)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Why It Shows Git Commits Instead of File Contents\n\nThe design is **intentional**: The Prompts section displays **git history** to show how prompt files have evolved over time. When you expand the `<details>` element, you see:\n\n1. A list of commits that modified each prompt file\n2. Each entry shows: Short SHA + Date + Commit message\n3. Click any entry to see the `git diff` showing what changed in that commit\n\n**It does NOT show file contents directly** because:\n- The focus is on tracking changes (audit trail)\n- Users can see the evolution of prompts across commits\n- The diff view shows what was added/removed in each commit\n\n---\n\n## Key CSS Classes (style.css):\n\n```css\n/* Details/pre styling (lines 197-221) */\ndetails { margin: 0.5rem 0; }\ndetails summary { cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; }\ndetails pre { background: var(--bg-surface); max-height: 400px; overflow: auto; }\n\n/* Diff block styling (lines 550-563) */\n.diff-block {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    padding: 0.5rem;\n    font-family: var(--mono);\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    max-height: 300px;\n    overflow: auto;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Important Implementation Details:\n\n1. **Git Integration**: Uses `os/exec` to run `git log` and `git diff` commands directly\n2. **Project Root**: All paths are relative to the project directory (`dir`)\n3. **Prompt File Location**: `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n4. **History Format**: `git log --format=%H %aI %s` (Full SHA, ISO8601 date, subject)\n5. **Diff Validation**: SHA is validated as hexadecimal before use (prevents command injection)\n6. **Styling**: Uses CSS `<details>` elements for expandable sections with `.diff-block` pre-formatted text\n\n---\n\n## Related Endpoints:\n\nThere are other file/content endpoints that serve **actual file contents** (not git history):\n\n- **`handleAPIStepContent`** (lines 1134-1199): Serves step prompt/script files from disk\n- **`handleAPIStepOutput`** (lines 563-634): Serves step execution output logs\n- **`handleAPIWorkflows`** (lines 1058-1132): Parses workflow DSL files\n\nBut these are different from the Prompts section, which is exclusively git-history-based."}],"totalDurationMs":24908,"totalTokens":54021,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1498,"cache_read_input_tokens":50706,"output_tokens":1812,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1498},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
